                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "Over his 20 years as an assignment photographer for National Geographic, Paul Nicklen has witnessed first-hand the beauty and wonder of the natural world, from playful penguins to terrifying leopard seals. But he has also seen how it is suffering, with habitats lost and species pushed to the brink of extinction. Nicklen has made it his life’s mission to show the world what is happening in the seas and polar regions through his stunning photography and believes it is not too late to inspire action and save them."
                    },
